es as mere extensions of the range of human freedoms. Modern ethics thus fails to take into account the moral intuition that some possibilities in the realm of techno science simply ought not to be pursued. A comprehensive assessment of modern western society's commitment to technological progress, The End of Ethics in a Technological Society presents a convincing argument in favour of a post-liberal approach - one that rejects the ideology of progress, supports caution, and accepts limitation."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aPHILOSOPHY / Ethics & Moral Philosophy.2bisacsh1 aMarratto, Scott, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSchmidt, Lawrence E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077357498440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773574984423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773574984/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles